    "Name": "Ripper (BA)",
    "Details": "Produced for the LAAF as a battle armor platoon carrier, even with an XL engine the extra weight required limits the craft to a single Small Pulse Laser and one ton of heavy ferro-fibrous armor. The Ripper, built from proven components for maximum reliability, uses a fusion engine to give the vehicle a significant range, as well as a high top speed, so much that the infantry compartment is equipped with special acceleration couches to handle the strain of a high speed combat insertion.\n\n<b><color=#ffcc00>Fusion: Expensive engine that works in a Vacuum.</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#ffcc00>Movement: 12/18 Hex: 360/540 Meters.</color></b>\n\n<color=#ffcc00><b>Armor:</b> Heavy Ferro-Fibrous\n<b>Structure:</b> Structure\n<b>Values       A        S  </b>\n<b>Front</b>        35      5\n<b>Left</b>          20      5\n<b>Right</b>        20      5\n<b>Rear</b>         10      5\n\n<b>Total</b>       95     25</color>\n\n<color=#ff0000>Quirk: Narrow/Low Profile</color>",
